in library at  west th avenue and several branches brunswick branch w e b dubois branch j f kennedy branch tolleston branch and woodson branch in march  the gary library board voted to close the main library on th avenue and the tolleston branch in what officials said was their best economic option the main library closed at the end of  the building now houses a museum  lake county public library operates the black oak branch at  west th avenue in the gary city limits in addition indiana university northwest operates the john w anderson library on its campus policeedit gary is served by the gary police department and the lake county sheriff historical photo of the gary fire department in  fire departmentedit the gary fire department gfd provides fire protection and emergency medical services to the city of gary transportationedit gptc gary public transportation corporation a commuter bus system that offers service to numerous stops throughout the city and neighboring suburbs gptc also has express service to locations outside of the city including connections to chicago transit front door pickup is available for disabled citizens at no extra cost gyy garychicago international airport is operating as the third airport for the chicago area it is undergoing much federally funded expansion and the administration is courting airlines aggressively boeing already bases its corporate fleets herecitation needed the national guard is intending to base its chicago area air operation there as well which would add much needed security to the airport interstate  indiana toll road interstate  interstate  and interstate  run through gary as well as us routes  and  indiana state road cline avenue and a former stretch of indiana state road  now decommissioned nictd northern indiana commuter transportation district operates the south shore line a commuter rail system one of the united states last original operating interurban railway systems running between chicago and south bend arts and cultureedit arts and filmedit a nightmare on elm street being filmed in gary the  urban movie original gangstas was filmed in the city the movie starred gary native fred williamson pam grier jim brown richard roundtree and isabel sanford among others since the early s gary has experienced a surge of hollywood filmmakers wishing to shoot movies in the city in  scenes for the remake of a nightmare on elm street were filmed in gary scenes from transformers dark of the moon wrapped up filming on august   the history channel documentary life after people was filmed in rundown and derelict parts of gary indiana meredith willsons  broadway musical the music man featured the song gary indiana in which lead character and con man professor harold hill wistfully recalls his alleged hometown in the play hill claims to be an alumnus of gary conservatory of music class of  but his entire reference to gary is later revealed to be another of his lies as the city of gary was not founded until  willsons musical set in  later was the basis of a film  and a television film  historic places on the national registeredit st augustines episcopal church ralph waldo emerson school barney sablotney house morningside historic district theodore roosevelt high school polk street concrete cottage historic district polk street terraces historic district van buren terrace historic district west fifth avenue apartments historic district miller town hall american sheet and tin mill apartment building louis j bailey branch librarygary international institute gary land company building gary city center historic district jacksonmonroe terraces historic district jefferson street historic district knights of columbus building horace mann historic district gary public schools memorial auditorium sportsedit the us steel yard home of the gary southshore railcats the following sports franchises are based in gary the gary southshore railcats are an american association professional baseball team the team plays in garys us steel yard baseball stadium the railcats played in the northern league from  until  and now play in the modern american association the team won league championships in   and  the gary splash are an international basketball league professional basketball team the team plays at the genesis convention center formerly the gary steelheads played in the genesis convention center as part of the ibl cba usbl and ibl educationedit there are three school districts serving the city and multiple charter schools located within the city public schoolsedit most public schools in gary are administered by the gary community school corporation the other public schools within the city are administered by lake ridge schools corporation which is the school system for the black oak neighborhood and unincorporated calumet township due to annexation law black oak residents retained their original school system and were not required to attend gary public schools charter schoolsedit charter schools in indiana including those in gary are granted charters by one of a small number of chartering institutions indiana charter schools are generally managed in cooperation between the chartering institution a local board of parents and community members salaried school administrators and a management company charter schools in gary as of  include thea bowman leadership academy charter school of the dunes gary lighthouse charter school formerly blessed sacrament parish and grade school and st century charter higher educationedit gary is home to two regional state college campuses indiana university northwest ivy tech community college northwest mediaedit newspapers – gary is served by two major newspapers based outside the city and by a garybased largely africanamerican interest paper these papers provide regional topics and cover events in gary the posttribune originally the gary posttribune is now based in merrillville a suburb of gary the times previously known as the hammond times offices and facilities for the times are in nearby munster the gary crusader based in gary and largely focused on black or africanamerican interests and readership the info newspaper based in gary and largely focused on black or africanamerican interests and readership the chicago tribune and the chicago suntimes are also distributed in gary broadcast – gary is served by five local broadcasters plus government access and numerous chicago area radio and tv stations and by other nearby stations in illinois and indiana whnwld channel  a repeater of leseas whme in south bend wpwrtv channel  is the chicago cw and mynetworktv affiliate but is licensed to gary studios and transmitters are colocated with wflds in chicago and like wfld wpwr is owned by fox television stations wyin channel  is a pbs affiliate licensed to gary their studios are in merrillville wgve fm  is owned by the gary community school corporation and is used primarily as a teaching facility programming is maintained by students in the broadcast program at the gary career center wgve also carries limited npr programming wlth am  carries syndicated talk programming and is owned by pluria marshall jr wwca am  is a relevant radio ownedandoperated radio station carrying programming from the catholicoriented relevant radio network notable peopleedit this section needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed october  learn how and when to remove this template message the jacksonsedit michael jacksons childhood home in gary indiana shortly after the singers death in  gary is the hometown of the jackson  a family of musicians who influenced the sound of modern popular music in  joseph and katherine jackson moved from east chicago indiana into their two bedroom house at  jackson st in gary indiana after they were married on november   the famous siblings would later record a song entitled  jackson street in  the jackson family members maureen reillette rebbie jackson born may   sigmund esco jackie jackson born may   toriano adaryll tito jackson born october   jermaine la jaune jackson born december   la toya yvonne jackson born may   marlon david jackson born march   michael joseph jackson august   – june   steven randall randy jackson born october   janet damita jo jackson born may   other notable peopleedit frank borman former astronaut for nasa and a retired united states air force colonel orsten artis ncaa champion with the historic texas western miners basketball team dan barreiro sports radio talk show host bob benoit – hollywood park racetrack chief executive albert m bielawski early th century michigan politician frank borman born  astronaut on gemini  and apollo  former ceo of eastern air lines lyman bostock – major league baseball player for california angels and minnesota twins john brim – bluesman donna britt washington post journalist and author avery brooks born  born in evansville actor director best known for star trek deep space nine vic bubas born  head basketball coach at duke university  vivian carter – music producer cofounder of veejay records label john chickerneo – nfl player alan roger currie born  author public speaker radio personality tony desantis – founder of drury lane theaters polly draper born  actress karen freemanwilson born  indiana attorney general attorney politician harry flournoy basketball player freddie gibbs born  rapper tom harmon –  heisman trophy winner for michigan sportscaster father of actor mark harmon latroy hawkins born  mlb pitcher for  years eric hillman born  mlb and japan pitcher gerald irons born  nfl player johnny jackson – drummer for the jackson  murdered in gary in  jason johnson born  nfl player tank johnson born  nfl player alex karras – winner of outland trophy member of college football hall of fame nfl player and actor blazing saddles webster robert kearns – inventor of intermittent windshield wiper systems subject of flash of genius ron kittle born  chicago white sox outfielder and  american league rookie of the year recipient bob kuechenberg born  nfl lineman twotime super bowl champion with miami dolphins karl malden – born in chicago oscarwinning actor william marshall  stage and film actor lloyd mcclendon born  professional baseball player manager of pittsburgh pirates seattle mariners robert a mcdonald born  ceo of procter  gamble and secretary of veterans affairs under president barack obama brandon moore born  nfl player sista monica parker – electric blues blues rock gospel and soul singer songwriter and record producer jerilynn patton known as jlin electronic musician jon petrovich – television executive for cnn dan plesac born  major league baseball pitcher with an year career now a mlb network analyst jesse powell born  recording artist elizabeth brown pryor – author and diplomat jimmy reed musician in blues hall of fame glenn robinson born  nba player and leagues no  draft pick father of glenn robinson iii glenn robinson iii born  nba player paul samuelson – economist recipient of the john bates clark medal  and the nobel prize  helene stanley  film actress joseph stiglitz born  economist recipient of the john bates clark medal  and the nobel prize  hank stram – nfl head coach – member of pro football hall of fame jeanne stunyo born  diver olympic silver medalist ernest lee thomas born  actor whats happening deniece williams born  grammy awardwinning rb artist fred williamson born  nfl player actor director producer tony zale – twice middleweight champion member of international boxing hall of fame sister citiesedit fuxin peoples republic of china lagos nigeria see alsoedit chicago portal indiana portal list of tallest buildings in gary northwest indiana neighborhoods in gary indiana referencesedit  a b c us geological survey geographic names information system city of gary   public officials directory lake county board of elections and vo